canonical:
  title: 禪源寺淸遠樓
  author: 釋達全
  language: lzh
  text: 不費登攀自曠然四郊爲圃海爲川蒲帆朝過有情吹茆棟晚生何處煙野抱山還山抱野天吞水亦水吞天般般形勝誰家具榧兀明䆫有毳禪
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 禪源寺淸遠樓
  author: 釋達全
  language: lzh
  text: 不費登攀自曠然。四郊爲圃海爲川。蒲帆朝過有情吹。茆棟晚生何處煙。野抱山還山抱野。天吞水亦水吞天。般般形勝誰家具。榧兀明䆫有毳禪。
korean:
  title: 선원사 청원루
  author: 석달전
  language: kor
  text: |-
    구태여 높은 산 안 올라도 마음이 활짝
    넓은 들이 삼밭이요 바다가 내로세
    아침결 지나는 배는 유정한 고동 소리
    저녁 무렵 초가집에 연기 나는 곳 어디인가
    들이 산을 안았는가, 산이 들을 안았는가
    하늘이 물을 삼켰는데 물이 역시 하늘 삼켰네
    갖가지 절승한 경개를 누가 갖추었나
    밝은 창 맑은 책상 납의 입은 중이 앉았구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0170_010_0870&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: The Pure Distance Pavilion at Seonwonsa Temple
  author: Seok Dal-jeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    No need to climb the mountain steep—
    the mind expands in boundless breadth.
    The wide fields become hemp gardens,
    the sea itself a flowing stream.

    At dawn, the sail-boats drift past,
    their emotional calls upon the wind.
    By evening, in a thatched cottage,
    where does that smoke drift from?

    Do the fields embrace the mountains,
    or mountains cradle all the fields?
    The sky consumes the waters whole,
    yet waters too consume the sky.

    All these magnificent vistas—
    who has gathered them as one?
    A monk sits in robes of down
    by the bright window, pure desk clear.
  footnotes:
    - The poem describes viewing the landscape from the Clear Distance Pavilion (청원루), achieving spiritual clarity without physical effort—a Buddhist concept of enlightenment.
    - The paradox of mutual consumption between sky and water reflects the Buddhist principle of interdependence and the dissolution of subject-object duality.
    - The final image of the monk contemplating the gathered vistas suggests that the natural beauty serves as a path to Buddhist awakening.
